replies.bodyText:
Understood that intention before making this change. With the rootProject approach:

gradle adds build folder at the root and does not clean it after with ./gradlew clean;
it increases the exposure of the servicetalk-grpc-protoc plugin for the whole project, that is not necessary if could be isolated in the module that is using it. Because the overhead of this task is very low, it's ok to run it for each module that needs it. Optimization doesn't worth it. Debugging of the gradle's task dependency graph and sequencing of tasks is easier when everything executes as part of a single module.

